attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, ARM, EABI4 version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, with debug_info, not stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a sophisticated IoT botnet agent, likely a variant of Mirai or a similar family, designed for ARMv7 architectures. It exhibits multiple malicious behaviors including vulnerability scanning and exploitation targeting Huawei HomeGateway (via /ctrlt/DeviceUpgrade_1), Realtek (via /picsdesc.xml), and Zyxel devices (via /cgi-bin/ViewLog.asp). It establishes command-and-control (C2) communication with 104.168.101.27, sending a bot identifier and awaiting commands. It contains a 'killer' module to terminate competing malware processes, a Telnet brute-force scanner with hardcoded credentials, and a DDoS attack module (attack_method_std). Notable signatures include the User-Agent 'r00ts3c-owned-you' and various shell command strings for downloading and executing additional payloads like 'resgod.arm7'.
